<Flashcard
    id="sql-1"
    tags={["programming", "SQL"]}
    source="sql.astro"
    references={["https://www.w3schools.com/sql/sql_create_table.asp"]}
>
    <Fragment slot="front">
        <h3>How do you create a table using SQL?</h3>
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="back">
        <CodeBlock
            lang="sql"
            code={`CREATE TABLE users (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, 
    username TEXT 
);`}
        />
        <CodeBlock
            lang="sql"
            code={`CREATE TABLE table_name (
    column1 datatype,
    column2 datatype,
    column3 datatype,
   ....
);`}
        />
    </Fragment>
</Flashcard>

<Flashcard
    id="sql-2"
    tags={["programming", "SQL"]}
    source="sql.astro"
    references={[
        "https://sqlite.org/autoinc.html#:~:text=Summary,a%2064%2Dbit%20signed%20integer.",
    ]}
>
    <Fragment slot="front">
        <h3>
            What is the difference of INTEGER and INT in SQLite when using them
            as a primary key?
        </h3>
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="back">
        <p>
            When we use INTERGER in a primary key it will auto increment whereas
            INT will not. This is because INTEGER PRIMARY KEY is the special
            alias for ROWID in SQLite.
        </p>
        <CodeBlock
            lang="sql"
            code={`CREATE TABLE users (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, 
    username TEXT 
);`}
        />
        <p>
            Here the entries in the "id" column will <strong>NOT</strong> auto increment.
        </p>
        <CodeBlock
            lang="sql"
            code={`CREATE TABLE users_bad (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    username TEXT
);`}
        />
    </Fragment>
</Flashcard>

